===================================================================
General-purpose .gitignore for Flutter projects.
Sections are organized to make it easy to understand and modify.
===================================================================
==> Secrets and Environment Variables <==
ALWAYS ignore files containing sensitive data like API keys or passwords.
This is the most critical section for security.
.env
*.keystore
/android/key.properties

==> IDE and Editor Configurations <==
User-specific settings for editors like VS Code, Android Studio, and IntelliJ.
.idea/
.vscode/
.atom/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws

==> Flutter & Dart Build Artifacts and Cache <==
These files are generated by the build process and can always be recreated.
.dart_tool/
.flutter-plugins
.flutter-plugins-dependencies
.pub/
.pub-cache/
build/
coverage/

Generated API documentation
**/doc/api/

==> Platform-Specific Build Artifacts and Configurations <==
Ignore files generated by the Android and iOS build toolchains.
Android
/android/.gradle
/android/app/debug
/android/app/profile
/android/app/release
/android/gradle
/android/gradlew
/android/gradlew.bat

This file contains the path to the Android SDK, which is machine-specific.
/android/local.properties

iOS
/ios/Flutter/.last_build_id
/ios/.symlinks/
/ios/Pods/
/ios/Runner.xcworkspace/
/ios/Runner.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace/
/ios/Runner.xcodeproj/xcuserdata/
/ios/DerivedData/
.swiftpm/

==> Symbolication and Obfuscation Maps <==
These are generated for debugging release builds and should not be in source control.
app..symbols
app..map.json

==> Operating System Files <==
Ignore files automatically generated by macOS, Windows, or Linux.
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

==> Logs and Temporary Files <==
General log files and temporary artifacts from various tools.
*.class
*.log
*.pyc
*.swp
.buildlog/
.history
migrate_dir/

==> Other Version Control Systems <==
Ignore metadata from other VCS like Subversion.
.svn/